# FreshLens — Project Context

**CS3203 · Group 21 · PID 5** · Repo: `FreshLens-AI/FreshLens-AI`

Multi-tenant SaaS for small grocery vendors. Phone camera → CNN classifies produce (Fresh / Medium / Spoiled) → dashboards + alerts.

**Roles:** Vendor (mobile) · Platform Admin (web)

## Monorepo — put code in the right place

| Path | Stack |
|------|-------|
| `apps/api/` | FastAPI (Python, async) |
| `apps/web/` | Next.js App Router + TypeScript |
| `apps/mobile/` | React Native (Expo) |
| `packages/ml/` | PyTorch CNN + Celery inference worker |
| `infra/db/migrations/` | Postgres schema + RLS |
| `infra/docker/` | Docker Compose |
| `docs/` | SRS, design, feasibility (course docs) |

## Approved stack only

FastAPI · PostgreSQL + RLS · Supabase Auth (prototype) · Next.js · Expo · Celery + Redis · Cloudflare R2 · Docker Compose · GitHub Actions

## Never introduce

- Node/NestJS backend (FastAPI only)
- Second queue system alongside Celery + Redis
- Un-namespaced Redis keys
- Sync CNN inference in API handlers
- DB table without `tenant_id` + RLS in the same migration
- Secrets in git (`.env`, keys, tokens)

